                  <TextArea editable="false" layoutX="14.0" layoutY="14.0" prefHeight="353.0" prefWidth="400.0" text="1. Introduction&#10;Purpose&#10;&#10;The Simple Text Editor is a lightweight and user-friendly application designed for creating, editing, and formatting plain text documents. It's suitable for tasks such as note-taking, writing essays, or editing code.&#10;Features&#10;&#10;    Creating, opening, and saving plain text documents.&#10;    Basic text manipulation (typing, deleting, selecting).&#10;    Undo and redo functionality.&#10;    Copy, cut, and paste text.&#10;    Text formatting options (font styles, sizes, colors, alignment).&#10;    Find and replace functionality.&#10;    Adjustable view options (zoom, word wrap).&#10;&#10;2. Getting Started&#10;Installation&#10;&#10;Download and install the Simple Text Editor from the provided source (website, app store, etc.) and follow the installation instructions for your operating system.&#10;Opening the Text Editor&#10;&#10;Double-click the application icon to open the Simple Text Editor.&#10;User Interface Overview&#10;&#10;The main window consists of:&#10;&#10;    Menu bar: Contains various menus (File, Edit, Format, etc.).&#10;    Toolbar: Provides quick access to commonly used actions.&#10;    Text area: The space where you can type and edit text.&#10;    Status bar: Displays information about the current document (word count, cursor position, etc.).&#10;&#10;3. Creating and Opening Documents&#10;Creating a New Document&#10;&#10;    Click on the &quot;File&quot; menu.&#10;    Select &quot;New&quot; to create a new, empty document.&#10;    Start typing in the text area.&#10;&#10;Opening Existing Documents&#10;&#10;    Click on the &quot;File&quot; menu.&#10;    Select &quot;Open&quot; and browse your computer to locate the desired text document.&#10;    Click &quot;Open&quot; to load the document.&#10;&#10;Saving Documents&#10;&#10;    Click on the &quot;File&quot; menu.&#10;    Select &quot;Save&quot; to save the document with its current name and location.&#10;    Select &quot;Save As&quot; to choose a new name and location for the document.&#10;&#10;4. Editing Text&#10;Basic Text Manipulation&#10;&#10;    To type: Simply start typing in the text area.&#10;    To delete: Use the backspace or delete key.&#10;    To select text: Click and drag over the desired text with the mouse cursor.&#10;&#10;Undo and Redo&#10;&#10;    To undo: Click &quot;Undo&quot; in the Edit menu or use the keyboard shortcut (e.g., Ctrl+Z).&#10;    To redo: Click &quot;Redo&quot; in the Edit menu or use the keyboard shortcut (e.g., Ctrl+Y).&#10;&#10;Copy, Cut, and Paste&#10;&#10;    To copy: Select text and click &quot;Copy&quot; in the Edit menu or use the keyboard shortcut (e.g., Ctrl+C).&#10;    To cut: Select text and click &quot;Cut&quot; in the Edit menu or use the keyboard shortcut (e.g., Ctrl+X).&#10;    To paste: Place the cursor where you want to paste and click &quot;Paste&quot; in the Edit menu or use the keyboard shortcut (e.g., Ctrl+V).&#10;&#10;5. Formatting Text&#10;Font Styles&#10;&#10;    Select text.&#10;    In the Format menu, choose the desired font style (bold, italic, underline).&#10;&#10;Font Sizes&#10;&#10;    Select text.&#10;    In the Format menu, select the desired font size.&#10;&#10;Text Colors&#10;&#10;    Select text.&#10;    In the Format menu, choose the desired text color.&#10;&#10;Alignment&#10;&#10;    Select text.&#10;    In the Format menu, choose alignment options (left, center, right).&#10;&#10;6. Find and Replace&#10;Searching for Text&#10;&#10;    Click on the &quot;Edit&quot; menu.&#10;    Select &quot;Find&quot; or use the keyboard shortcut (e.g., Ctrl+F).&#10;    Enter the text you want to find and click &quot;Find Next.&quot;&#10;&#10;Replacing Text&#10;&#10;    Click on the &quot;Edit&quot; menu.&#10;    Select &quot;Replace&quot; or use the keyboard shortcut (e.g., Ctrl+H).&#10;    Enter the text to find and the text to replace it with.&#10;    Click &quot;Replace&quot; or &quot;Replace All&quot; to make the changes.&#10;&#10;7. View Options&#10;Zooming In and Out&#10;&#10;    In the View menu, select the desired zoom level.&#10;&#10;Word Wrap&#10;&#10;    In the View menu, enable or disable word wrap to adjust how text wraps within the text area.&#10;&#10;8. Keyboard Shortcuts&#10;&#10;    New: Ctrl + N&#10;    Open: Ctrl + O&#10;    Save: Ctrl + S&#10;    Save As: Ctrl + Shift + S&#10;    Undo: Ctrl + Z&#10;    Redo: Ctrl + Y&#10;    Copy: Ctrl + C&#10;    Cut: Ctrl + X&#10;    Paste: Ctrl + V&#10;    Find: Ctrl + F&#10;    Replace: Ctrl + H&#10;    Zoom In: Ctrl + +&#10;    Zoom Out: Ctrl + -&#10;    Word Wrap: Ctrl + Shift + W&#10;&#10;9. FAQs&#10;&#10;Q: Can I open documents from other text editors?&#10;A: Yes, you can open plain text documents created in other editors with the Simple Text Editor.&#10;&#10;Q: Is there an autosave feature?&#10;A: No, the Simple Text Editor does not have an autosave feature. Remember to save your work regularly.&#10;10. Troubleshooting&#10;&#10;    If the application freezes, try closing and reopening it.&#10;    If you encounter formatting issues, try saving and reopening the document.&#10;    For more complex functionalities, consider using a more advanced text editor or word processor." />
